1
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:04,500
After I left prison I didn’t step outside
the house for about a year and a half

2
00:00:05,416 --> 00:00:06,583
I was ashamed in front of people

3
00:00:08,125 --> 00:00:10,125
People don’t know the truth

4
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:15,458
Even my uncle,
my mother’s brother

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,916
Says to me—If you hadn’t done something,
they wouldn’t have cut off your hand

6
00:00:19,791 --> 00:00:22,083
So what will strangers say

7
00:00:22,875 --> 00:00:24,625
For that reason

8
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:28,958
I didn’t even mix with my
brothers and sisters at home

9
00:00:29,416 --> 00:00:31,291
I went out and came back alone

10
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:35,333
In the days of ISIS, when
there were no cell phones

11
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:42,916
At that time I desperately wanted
some relief, I was looking for ease

12
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:46,291
Because of what I saw in
detention and the injustice

13
00:00:48,291 --> 00:00:50,916
And my brother had a cell phone

14
00:00:51,666 --> 00:00:54,583
I took it from him
and kept using it

15
00:00:54,583 --> 00:00:56,958
For two or three months,
then I gave it back to him

16
00:00:58,166 --> 00:01:01,583
I stayed at home all the
time until I met a friend

17
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:08,958
This is my friend

18
00:01:10,625 --> 00:01:12,625
More than a brother

19
00:01:14,791 --> 00:01:18,250
When I started going out to the
street after that year and a half

20
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:22,041
When I went out, I
didn’t raise my head

21
00:01:22,458 --> 00:01:23,875
I kept my head down
toward the ground

22
00:01:23,916 --> 00:01:24,875
And my hand was in my pocket

23
00:01:27,708 --> 00:01:30,333
So he began encouraging
me, walking with me

24
00:01:31,750 --> 00:01:33,666
He walked with
me wherever I went

25
00:01:36,625 --> 00:01:40,125
Many of his friends told
him—Don’t walk with him

26
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,708
He’s suspicious and
will ruin your reputation

27
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:45,083
He told them—It’s
none of your business

28
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:48,333
This is my affair and I
want to accompany him

29
00:01:48,583 --> 00:01:51,583
And he’s still with me,
always encouraging me

30
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:55,000
Because of him I started
taking my hand out in the street

31
00:01:55,458 --> 00:01:57,750
I walk proudly and don’t
pay attention to anyone

32
00:01:58,250 --> 00:02:00,166
And I don’t listen to
this one or that one

33
00:02:00,208 --> 00:02:02,083
And thank God
